Job redesign is the process of revisiting and restructuring jobs to meet the specific needs of a particular segment of the workforce.  Job redesign process  Advantages of job redesigning  Therefore, the purpose of job redesigning is to identify the task significance and skill variety available in the organization and reallocate the job-related tasks and responsibilities according to the specific skills possessed by an employee. By World Economic Forum | 3 days ago By World Economic Forum | 3 days ago By Tony Mbaya | 6 days ago By Tony Mbaya | 14 days ago